@startuml budget-exchange
' The budget counter exchange: four data movements at four cadences, and what is not on the enforcement path.
' Source of truth: docs/src/gateways/llm/budgets-and-rate-limits.md
!include _style.puml

participant "Gateway\nReplica-0" as r0 #90EE90
participant "Gateway\nReplica-1" as r1 #90EE90
participant "kaalm-budget-{provider}\nConfigMap" as cm #FFD580
participant "ModelProvider\nReconciler" as rec #87CEEB

== Startup ==

r0 -> cm : read **_canonical**
cm --> r0 : the current period's spent value
note over r0, cm
  **This is the only time a replica reads _canonical.**
  After startup it never reads that key again.
end note

== 1. Per request (in-memory) ==

loop every LLM call
  r0 -> r0 : increment the in-memory counter,\nsynchronously, per\n(provider, namespace, period)
end

== 2. Every 10s (server-side apply) ==

loop every 10s
  r0 -> cm : **SSA** key **"kaalm-gateway-0"**\nfield manager = **its own Pod name**\n'{"period": "2026-04", "team-support": "142.50"}'
  r1 -> cm : **SSA** key **"kaalm-gateway-1"**\nfield manager = **its own Pod name**
end
note over cm
  Each replica owns **exactly one key** via its own field
  manager, so simultaneous writes never conflict. The
  **period** tag lets the reducer drop stale entries during
  rollover, when replicas transition independently.
end note

== 3. On every ConfigMap change (watch) ==

loop watch event
  cm --> r0 : changed
  r0 -> r0 : fold **peers' current-period partials**\ninto its enforcement view
end
note over r0, cm #FFE4B5
  **Load-bearing.** The value a replica enforces against is
  its own live counter **plus every peer's latest partial**,
  at most one 10s write interval stale. Without this fold,
  a long-lived replica would never observe peer spend and
  enforcement drift would grow **unbounded** within a period.
end note

== 4. Each reconcile (event-driven + 5m requeue) ==

rec -> cm : read all keys
cm --> rec : per-replica partials
rec -> rec : **filter** out entries whose **period**\nis not the current period\n**prune** keys with no live gateway Pod name\n**sum** the remaining partials
rec -> cm : write **_canonical**
rec -> rec : update ModelProvider **status.budgetUsage**

note over r0, rec #FFE4B5
  **_canonical is NOT on the enforcement path.**
  It is the durable roll-up: status reporting, and the value
  a replica initializes from on (re)start. Per-request
  enforcement reads peers' partials straight off the watch
  and never waits on the reconciler.
end note
@enduml
